Colin Pitchfork was jailed for life in 1988 for raping and killing two schoolgirls in 1983 . 
  He strangled 15-year-old Lynda Mann to death in the Leicestershire village of Narborough . 
  Three years later he raped and killed Dawn Ashworth less than a mile away . 
  He was the first man to be convicted on the basis of DNA evidence . 
  He received a 30-year minimum sentence which was cut to 28 years in 2009 . 
  Parole Board is reviewing his suitability for release next year . 
 